                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="title" --> 
                  <td align="left" class="maintitle"><strong>PGCE Secondary Education - Modern Foreign Languages (French: R1X1; German R2X1; Spanish R4X1; Urdu X1ZX1) </strong></td>
                  <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></tr>
                <tr> 
                  <td align="left" class="bodytext">&nbsp; </td>
                </tr>
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="main text" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="10" class="greypicbox">
                      <tr>
                        <td class="bodytext"><strong>NEW: PGCE in MFL : URDU FOR  SEPTEMBER 2007</strong><br>
The College is including Urdu in the range of languages offered in its PGCE  programme (for 14-19 age range) for September 2007. There are only 10 places  available. Students should apply to Trinity &amp; All Saints via the <a href="http://www.gttr.ac.uk/"><strong>GTTR</strong></a> immediately as there will be  competition for these limited places. Applicants should have an honours degree  and either have studied Urdu as part of their degree or be a native speaker of  Urdu. For more information please contact Anne Welburn on <a href="mailto:a.welburn@leedstrinity.ac.uk"><strong>a.welburn@leedstrinity.ac.uk</strong></a> or phone 0113 2837268.</td>
                      </tr>
                    </table><p>The course will equip  you with the knowledge, understanding and practical skills required to pursue a  successful career in teaching. You will develop your skills in planning,  delivering and assessing lessons in your main subject. </p>
                    <p>You should  also be able to contribute effectively to the cross-curricular provision of  your school. You will learn to cater for the variety of intellectual, social  and moral needs of pupils in schools and will become aware of the changing  nature of teaching in a complex, multicultural society.</p>
                    <p>This PGCE  programme is for graduates of French, German, Spanish or Urdu who wish to teach  in secondary schools. Although the course provides a final qualification in one  language only, during the course you can have experience in the classroom in a  second language. This will be detailed in your references and Career Entry  Profile.<br>
                        <br>
                      We are a centre for excellence in modern languages resources and language  training for business. We offer training schemes for teachers and have  well-established international links. <a href="http://www.tasc.ac.uk/depart/COMENIUS/index.htm"><strong>The Comenius  Centre</strong></a>, run on behalf of the Centre for Information on Language  Teaching and Research (CILT) has been based at Trinity &amp; All Saints since  1994. </p>
                    <p>Training is  provided through progressive, practical and creative workshops. Learning is by  doing rather than by reading about teaching; there is a strong emphasis on  practical experience. Completion rates on the PGCE MFL course are very high as  are the employment rates for our graduates. Former students have been  successful in obtaining teaching posts across the UK  and Europe.</p>
                    <p><strong>Entry  Requirements</strong><strong><br>
                      </strong>A  degree in French, German, Spanish or Urdu is preferred. Native speakers of  French, German, Spanish or Urdu should hold a degree or degree equivalent. <br>
                      <br>
                      We do consider applications from individuals without a degree in modern foreign  languages but who hold a degree in a different discipline, provided they have  attained sufficient competence in a foreign language, and can demonstrate how  this has been achieved. <br>
  <br>
                      GCSE English and Mathematics at Grade C or above or equivalent qualification</p>
                    <p>We offer our  own internal Mathematics test to those who have a conditional place on the  course but who do not already have GCSE Maths</p>
                    <p><strong>Please  Note: </strong> </p>
                    <ul type="disc">
                      <li>Applicants with <strong>only one Modern Foreign Language</strong> can apply for this course. </li>
                      <li>Support for enhancement of       First Subject through in- house Subject Knowledge Booster Courses in       August prior to start of PGCE year </li>
                      <li>Support for enhancement of a       second subject through Extension courses (links with Hull:       French Extension Course and Newcastle:       German Extension Course) </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>The  Training Course </strong><br>
                      The programme runs for 37 weeks from September to July. At least 24 weeks of  training is school-based. There are three stages of training: <br>
                      <br>
                      STAGE 1 is based at Trinity &amp; All Saints and establishes the foundation of  knowledge and understanding necessary for you to benefit from school-based  training. <br>
                      <br>
                      STAGE 2 is school-based (school A) and seeks to provide the basic skills  necessary for you to function as a teacher.<br>
                      <br>
                      STAGE 3 is school-based (school B) where your skills will be refined and your  ability to transfer competence from one school to another will <br>
                      be tested. <br>
                      <em><br>
                      <em>Campus-based training</em></em> comprises: <br>
&bull; French, German, Spanish or Urdu Subject Application<br>
&bull; Professional Studies<br>
&bull; An optional unit in Catholic Education (if required)<br>
  <br>
  <em>School-based Training </em><br>
  Trinity &amp; All Saints has partnerships with many Catholic and  non-denominational schools: <br>
  <br>
&bull; Across the West Yorkshire region (Leeds, Bradford, Calderdale, Kirklees and  Wakefield) <br>
&bull; In the Northwest and Northeast (Scarborough, Preston, Manchester, Darlington) <br>
&bull; In South Yorkshire and Nottinghamshire <br>
  <br>
                      As far as possible, training schools will be allocated with reference to your  personal circumstances.<br>
                      <br>
                      <strong>Assessment</strong> <br>
                    In order to be eligible for Qualified Teacher Status (QTS), you must  demonstrate your ability to meet the assessment criteria laid down by Trinity  &amp; All Saints and the Department for Education and Skills/Teacher Training  Agency (DfES/TTA). </p>
                    <p>There are few  formal examinations; assessment is mainly by coursework assignments and by  performance in classroom teaching and training activities in schools. <br>
                        <br>
                        <strong>Facilities</strong><br>
                      Our new library and computer centre is well-stocked with a range of classroom  text books and other teaching resources, education books, journals,  audio-visual resources, CD-Rom databases and video and production facilities. <br>
  <br>
  <strong>How to Apply</strong><strong><br>
  </strong>Applications must be made through the Graduate Teacher Training Registry (<a href="http://www.gttr.ac.uk/"><strong>GTTR</strong></a>). There is no closing date but  you are encouraged to apply early so that we can advise you about the  appropriate preparation you will need to make prior to starting the course,  including observation in secondary school classrooms.<br>
  <br>
                      For an application pack:<br>
                      Telephone 0870 11 22 205<br>
                      Write to: GTTR, Rosehill, New Barn    Lane, Cheltenham,  Gloucestershire GL52 3LZ<br>
                      Apply online:<a href="http://www.gttr.ac.uk/how/index.html"><strong> www.gttr.ac.uk</strong></a><br>
  <br>
  <strong>Funding</strong> <br>
  <a href="http://www.tasc.ac.uk/studentfinance/PGCE%20help.htm"><strong>Find out more  information about PGCE Funding </strong></a></p>
                    <strong>More information...</strong><strong><br>
                    </strong>Website: <a href="http://www.leedstrinity.ac.uk/education/pgce/"><strong>http://www.leedstrinity.ac.uk/education/pgce/</strong></a><a href="http://www.tasc.ac.uk/education/pgce/"><strong><br>
                    </strong></a>Tel: 0113 283 7268<br>
Email: <a href="mailto:admissions@leedstrinity.ac.uk"><strong>admissions@leedstrinity.ac.uk</strong></a>
<p><br>
</p>
